 
<p>

  The ACLU told the Senate about the <a href="https://www.commondreams.org/newswire/aclu-strongly-opposes-cascade-of-dangerous-legislation-threatening-to-destroy-digital-privacy">danger of various bills</a> that would "protect children" by snooping on the communications of all adults.
<p>
  The ACLU <a href="https://www.engadget.com/bipartisan-senate-group-reintroduces-a-revised-kids-online-safety-act-212117992.html">opposes KOSA</a>, too, because it would require even more data collection
about every user to figure out who is a minor.

 